page.title: 16HOME LIFE
page.content: Saturday July 13: at 6.45 listened to radio: 8.00 got up, caught train to High Wycombe to shop.British Rail actually on time!.Macdonald's for lunch, then home to watch "Live Aid" concert on T.V. in aid of the African famine. Sunday:up at 9.30, 10.00 homework-two essays-then roast chicken for lunch, then homework, bed at 10.30. Monday: school,I imagine what my teachers have written in my reports. Cycling home,flies in my eyes as usual. Tuesday:raining so sports day cancelled and I had no books for my lessons. In biology we did dentition and counted our teeth. Watched T.V. Wednesday:lazy-watched sports -we won. Thursday:feel full, two bowls of raspberries eaten. Friday:physics today.Thumped Louise for teasing me and felt better.Must stop,Miss Kiely wants my "D"project.
